There are only two remains of the postcranial skeleton (1FIII and 2FIII). Both are robust and are within the range of variation of the phalanges of 

H. crassum

from Perpignan and Le Soler (Lit de la Têt) (
Alberdi & Aymar 1995
). On the other hand, they are identical, both in size and robustness to those of 

H.
cf. 
crassum

from Dorkovo (
Bulgaria
).
